-- Royal Bank’s Stymiest to Retire in June, Bank Says
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2010-12-10T22:16:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-10/royal-bank-of-canada-s-barbara-stymiest-to-retire-next-summer-bank-says.html
Royal Bank of Canada, the country’s
biggest bank, said executive  Barbara Stymiest  plans to retire in
June to focus on charities and corporate board work.  Stymiest, group head of strategy, treasury and corporate
services, will continue as an adviser to the Toronto-based bank
until she retires, Chief Executive Officer  Gordon Nixon  said
today in a memo to employees. Stymiest joined Royal Bank in 2004
as chief operating officer, after serving as CEO for Toronto
Stock Exchange owner TSX Group Inc.  Royal Bank also said it would start reorganizing management
roles effective Jan. 4.  Stymiest, 54, is a director of RBC Dexia Investor Services,
 Research In Motion Ltd.,  the Canadian Institute for Advanced
Research and the Royal Ontario Museum, according to a company
biography. She’s also been involved in charities including the
United Way.  To contact the reporter responsible for the story:
